# Project Evaluation Activity



__Project Name:__  Open Food Facts


---

## Finding info about contributing on the website.

In the following section you should only enter the information that you
found on the project website. Some of the answers will be impossible to find, others
may be very hard to find. Do not _google_ for answers.

__Project website:__ [Open Food Facts](https://world.openfoodfacts.org/)


__What is the purpose of the project:__ An open-data database where anyone can submit food items and their information.


__How easy was it to find information about contributing on the website?__ Very easy, there's a contribute page linked on their header.


__Contributing instructions:__ There's a [contributing page](https://world.openfoodfacts.org/contribute) on their website, and also on their [main organization page](https://github.com/openfoodfacts#how-can-i-help) on github as well. 

__URL for the code repository:__ [Code repository](https://github.com/openfoodfacts)

__Bug/Issue tracker link:__ There are many repositories inside the main organization for Open Food Facts that all contain their own issue tracker. [Here's an example](https://github.com/openfoodfacts/openfoodfacts-server/issues) of one repository's bug/issue tracker on GitHub.

__Mailing list:__ [Mailing list](https://blog.openfoodfacts.org/en/newsletter-2)

__Chat channel:__ [Slack channel](https://slack.openfoodfacts.org/)

__Other communication channels:__ [Forum](https://forum.openfoodfacts.org/)


