## Summary assesment
__How friendly is this project for beginner contributors?__ It looks really friendly for beginners! Their contribution page on their main website lists out many different ways to contribute, and greatly encourage joining their slack channel for more personalized and responsive chats.




__Do the maintainers respond helpfully to questions in issues?__ Yes but only sometimes. There are a lot of recent issues that don't have any comments/discussion, but the ones that do usually approach the issue in a nice manner.



__Are people friendly in the issues, discussion forum, and chat (for example, IRC or Slack)?__ Yes, after going through a few of the forum posts, many of the people there are welcoming and respond to posts nicely.




__Do pull requests get reviewed?__ For all the pull requests made in the last week (both opened and closed), about half of them got reviewed, and most of the ones that did get reviewed were pushed and closed.



__Do maintainers thank people for their contributions?__ No they do not.



__Are there special skills required to contribute to the project? If so, what are they?__ There aren't any specific skills required, since there's so many different ways that you can contribute and add to this project. Considering it is a website and also a mobile app, knowledge in JS, Swift, Java/Kotlin, and HTML/CSS would be the basics.



__Are there any special hardware/software requirements to be able to contribute to the project? If so, what are they?__ Needs Docker and Make installed on your computer, more of the specific instructions can be found [here](https://github.com/openfoodfacts/openfoodfacts-server/blob/main/docs/introduction/dev-environment-quick-start-guide.md).
